10. Qxb4
10. a5{ Surprisingly, this is a novelty. Makes more sense to play ... Na6 , ... Ndc5 , and ... a4  ideas. White has an extra pawn, but a very awkward piece set up, and we admire how the  d2 -knight completely messes up with White's coordination.     After the first step of our plan is done (castling there as well) we can follow up with  e7 -... e6  to break through the center and keep up with the pressure through our excellent knights and the  g7 - b2  diagonal. }
