11. fxe5
11. Ng4{ The rook on  f8  is excellent to defend threats through the  a2 - g8  diagonal and  f1 - f8  file. }
12. e6( 12.Bg5 { here is not really dangerous as }12...Qb6 13.O-O Ndxe5 { simply gives a winning position for Black. } )
12. Nde5{ White needs to castle eventually, but we'll show why they can't. }
13. exf7+
13. Rxf7
