14. a6
15. a4
15. Qa5{ A very young Kasparov played the conventional plan with ... Re8 -... Rc8  and then ... c5 -... c4  and ended up suffering a bit, even though he had a playable position.  ½-½   (48) Lapienis, D-Kasparov, G Baku 1978 .     After 15...  Qa5  we have similar intentions with ... c5 -... c4  and ... Nc5  and even ... Nfd7  later, but the active Queen gives extra worries to our opponent as ... Qb4  and  b7 -... b5  is always on the menu. }
