22. Rxf5{ And this insane streak of threats finishes with a win! Friendly reminder that this 9.  Nf3  variation serves as an example of tactical ideas and attacking/ defensive motifs. If you have to remember one thing, be this one: pay attention to every detail.     I barely knew any theory when I played the Benoni from not having ELO to 2400+, so I had to rely on ideas, plans, and more importantly, concrete calculation!. }
