14. Qe1{ The white queen provokes again our  e8 -rook. This time, the inclusion of  a3  and ... Ra7  makes it a bit more logical for white. }( 14.Bc2 { this prophylactic move serves white to get ahead of any ... c5 -... c4  ideas and asks us what to do }14...Nb6 { we always try to develop, and now we have the  c4 -square to our knight! We will follow up with ... N8d7  and then look for ... Nf6 . White played quite passively, and we are in time to develop everything smoothly. } )
14. f5{ We make good use of the pin and the  a7 -rook will definitely help our castle. }
