13. Ne5
14. Bf4
14. Nxf3+( { A game against the great theoretician and a Benoni expert followed with }14...Re8 15.Qd2 gxf5 16.Nxe5 Bxe5 17.Bxe5 Rxe5 18.Qh6 Qf8! { and White doesn't have anything better than drawing with  Qd8 +- Qg5 +.     I feel it's a great example of how the line is very practical for Black and how it doesn't matter that much how precise you play most of the time, as White needs to play clinical.  ½-½   (23) Shevchenko, K (2647)-Pantsulaia,L (2571) Terme Catez 2021 . } )
