12. a6{ Important intermediate move to kick the knight. }( { Is not really obvious that after }12...Nf6 13.Rxe8+ Nxe8 14.Bg5 { Black is struggling to counter White's initiative, but an 85% win rate might give you enough context for now🙂. Here White has a couple of main moves,  Na3  and  Nc3 , and we'll also check some minor options that are not dangerous. } )
13. Nc3{ Remember that we have some development to do yet. Here I'll recommend more practical variations without the need of taking the  c3 -pawn. }
13. Nxc3
14. bxc3
14. Rxe1+{ We can take on  c3 , but why bother? I feel this is much simpler. }
15. Qxe1
15. Bb7
16. Bg5
16. Qc8{ We will finish up the development with ... Nd7  and we are doing fine. In general, we don't want to freely allow  c3 - c4  for White, as it would mean killing the  b7 -bishop. Knowing that, I feel our play is extremely easy. }
17. Qe7{ This specific move is easily solved with precision. }
17. h6
18. Be3( { In case of }18.Bf4 Nd7! { and taking on  d6  would be easily countered by ... Bf8  and the  d5 -pawn will fall. } )
18. Bxd5
19. Qxd6
19. Qc6{ We will develop quickly the queenside and the  c3 -pawn would eventually fall. }
