18. Bxd4
19. Bc4{ After some engine moves that don't deserve much explanation (it just works, don't try to make it sense) the key idea for White is revealed. }
19. Qxc4
20. Qf3+
20. Bf5
21. Qxa8
21. Qb3{ We'll regroup with ... Nd7 , ... Be6  and even ... Qd5 , and we are doing great. ... c5 -... c4  might be a threat later on, or even ... Ne5 , ... Bxh3  ideas to kill our opponent's king.     We play around the fact that the  g5 -bishop is just controlling 'air' and doesn't create many threats, while our  d4 -bishop looks very good. }
