12. h3{ The best move for White. Prepares properly  f2 - f4  and still prevents  h7 - h5  as  Bg5 !, is so strong. }
12. Ne8{ We go on with the plan. }
13. Be2{ Smartest move. Already played twice. White patiently avoids all our tricks and counterplay. You see how hard it is for White, it's like a minefield. }
13. Nc7
14. Bf4{ The best move now again. It feels so odd how White needs to keep switching plans, as  f2 - f4  now was too slow against ... b5 ! }
14. Qe7
15. Qd2{ White needs to let us play ... b5 . From my experiences  a4 - a5  is always very tempting but here was far worse as we have pressure on  b2  and later on we would play ... Nb5  anyway but on our terms. }
15. b5
16. axb5
16. Nxb5( 16...axb5 17.Ra7 { would be painful. } )
17. Nxb5
17. axb5
18. Ra7
18. b4{ We'll follow up with ... Rb7 , and we have all the queenside fixed for a better endgame. After all this precise play, White only has a small edge, and we still have a very easy way to play and counterplay chances on the queenside. }
