8. Bg5{ The only really logical continuation. White wants to wait long enough, so we castle, and  Ng3  is finally available as ... h5 -... h4  won't be possible anymore. }( 8.Ng1!? { is an interesting way to punish ... h5 , seen in many variations  (for instance the Najdorf with 6.  h3  and 7.  Nde2 ) but we can just play as usual and ... h5  might even be useful when we play ... Bg4 , ... Bxf3 , ... Nh7  later on, as we talked about in another chapter. } )
