3. d5
3. e6
4. Nc3
4. exd5
5. cxd5
5. d6
6. e4
6. g6
7. Be2{ Swiercz recommends this move order as it is based more on strategy and placing the pieces into the correct squares, and less on crushing us.     It is certainly dangerous as White's play is easier than in other variations, and we need to play precise. White wants to go for  Nf3 - Nd2 - Nc4  later on and include  Bf4  somewhere in the middle to pressure  d6  and finish the development. }( { White usually prefers it of }7.Nf3 { as we can go for }7...a6!? 8.a4 Bg4 { as an extra option. For instance, Hou Yifan opted for this approach on many occasions. This is a recurring theme for Black, as ... Bg4  directly has some issues with  Qa4 +!, and after ... Nbd7 ,  Nd2  would leave the  g4 -bishop completely out of position and lost to  h3 - g4 . } )
7. Bg7
8. Nf3
8. Bg4{ This move order makes more sense. Technically, the reason is that including ... a6  and  a4  the  Nd2 - Nc4  variation is more interesting for White, but it also makes sense to play ... Bg4  straightforward when there is no threat of  Qa4 +.     We want to take on  f3  and then secure the  e5 -square with ... Qe7  or ... Re8  and ... Nbd7 . After the first part of the plan, we have ideas with ... h5 -... Nh7  that are incredibly interesting and powers up our  g7 -bishop and also allows for some  Ng5  or even  Qh4 . }
9. Nd2{ This was recently played by Wojtaszek against Rapport, and we will see how not including ... a6  and  a4  affects. }
9. Bxe2
10. Qxe2
10. O-O
11. Nc4
11. Nbd7{ As seen many times whenever White plays  Nd2 - Nc4 , we can sacrifice the pawn and strike back! }( { Now the pawn is taboo as }12.Nxd6? Qb8! 13.Nc4 b5! { followed by ... Re8 , and we gain too many tempos, kicking the knights out and also threatening the exposed center. Considering White didn't even castle yet, it is very promising.     If White doesn't come to take on  d6 , we can safely play ... Nb6  and then the usual ... Qe7  to defend  d6  and allow ... Nbd7 -... Ne5  as a maneuver to reroute our knight and keep track of the  c4 -knight. } )
