10. Nd2{ We are still following Swiercz. White wants to reroute the knight to  c4  and increase the pressure on  d6 . We are very happy to have the  c8 -bishop exchanged already, so we look forward to creating some counterplay. }
10. Bxe2
11. Qxe2
11. Nh5{ We force back the  f4 -bishop, so we can develop the  b8 -knight. }
12. Be3
12. Nd7
13. g4{ If White tries to do this expansion too soon, we have plenty of time to strike back. }
13. Nhf6
14. O-O
14. a6
15. a4
15. h5{ White is left with no suitable answer. }
16. h3( 16.g5 Ng4 17.Bf4 Nge5 {  c5-c4  is a very important move to have the  d3 -square available if needed, as White would try to make  Bxe5  and  f2 - f4  work in the next move. Now }18.Bxe5? Bxe5! 19.f4? Bxf4! { would win the game. } )
16. hxg4
17. hxg4
17. Ne5
18. g5
18. Nh5{ ... f5  is coming and White's castle is crumbling. }
