12. Ne5{ This was the correct answer and we have our excellent blockade. }( 12...Rb8?! 13.O-O Ne5 14.Nxe5 dxe5 { here we have a great example of how having the pawn on  e4  changes completely the picture. Now after  Be3  White pressures the exposed queenside, }15.Be3 Qc7 16.a5 c4 17.Bb6 { and I was already winning in:  1-0   (46) Alonso Rosell,A (2561)-Bauer,T (2145) Katowice 2022 . } )
13. O-O
13. Nxf3+
14. Qxf3
