7. Nd2{ One of the key topics about the Benoni is the  c4 -square. If White manages to put a Knight and secure the spot, it would be beneficial in many ways. Pressuring our weakness on  d6 , controlling the queenside (and the key square  b6  in case of  a7 -... a6 + a4 , ... a5  inclusion) and helping the center to push  f4 - e5  eventually.     A hidden idea that appears not too often is being able to jump to  a5  after an eventual  b7 -... b5 ,  axb5 ,  axb5 , as the  c6 -square might be somehow exposed. With this move order, we need to pay special attention to our moves to kick or counter the  c4 -knight at the right time, or we will be left tangled without much space and the  c8 -bishop complaining. }
7. Bg7
8. Nc4{ White usually enjoyed great advantage in this line historically. As we were forced to concede against the domination of the  Nc4  and the pressure on  d6  of the bishop. }
8. O-O
9. g3{ This weird move relies on us not being able to develop our queenside minor pieces normally. But here we will focus on exchanging the  c4 -knight again. }
9. Ng4{ With the Bishop on  c1 , giving up the  d6 -pawn doesn't imply so much counterplay as the  b2 -pawn is defended, and we don't have the recurring ... Nh5  winning a tempo. }
10. Bf4{ Only logical move, to prevent ... Ne5 . We want to keep the diagonal open and only in very specific cases do we choose to play ... dxe5  (a knight needs to come to  d6  later to block the passed  d -pawn). }
10. Nd7( { We transposed to the variation where White plays   }9.Bf4 Nbd7 10.g3!? { with the Knight on  g4 , the threat of ... g5 !, and ... Qf6 !, and pressuring  f2  or any shuffle of these moves is something very real and White needs to pay attention to it. } )( { For instance }11.Bxd6?! Re8 12.Bf4? g5! 13.Bd2 Qf6! { and White is busted as the position opens up too much and the king is still in the center. } )
11. Nxd6
11. g5
12. Bd2
12. Nxf2( { After }13.Kxf2 Qf6+ { we'll take the  d6 -knight and White would be left with an exposed king, and we will have excellent blockade and control through the dark squares. Moves like ... Re8  and ... c4  would be punishing. } )
