16. Qf6
17. g3( { In the case of }17.Be3!? Bd7! { followed by ... Nc7  feels enough as we complete our development and the  d6 -pawn is no longer completely defenseless. } )( { We don't go for }17...Ba6 { as }18.Qa4! Bxb5 19.Qxb5 { would be excellent for White as the  e4  knight is on a delicate spot and White got rid of one of the spare knights since  d6  was no longer a target. } )
17. Bh3{ We keep playing a forced variation. }
18. Re1
