24. Bd4+( 24...Nc7 { would be awful as }25.Nf5! { threats  Rg1  as well as  d5 - d6 . } )
25. Kf3
25. Nc7
26. Ke4
26. Ne8{ We threaten ... Nf6 + to get back the pawn, and White cannot even take on  e8  nor create any side threat.  ½-½   (55) Mendonca,L (2596)-Solodovnichenko,Y (2489) La Nucia 2023 .     This 7.  Nd2  has the most forcing lines I would say, but considering how we basically have only moves and White doesn't have alternatives to trick us, so I'd say it is a good investment to know well a long line that relies on pure counterplay and exemplifies very well the nature of the Benoni.     Also, bear in mind that we are looking at 2500+ games mostly, so this level of precision is not the usual. }
