13. Nd2( 13.Nh4!? { White can do a similar approach to isolate our knight on  e5 , }13...Nge5! 14.f4 Nc4 { we keep running, and we reallocate the knight on the other side of the board! Now suddenly ... Na5 , ... c4 , ... Nb3  is a huge threat, and we have all the pieces controlling the  e4 - e5  push.     The  Nh4  and  Bg2  are not very threatening to consider any kind of crazy attack on our king, so we will eventually expand through the queenside. } )
