9. Bb6
10. e3
10. f5
11. Be2{ The whole point of  Ne4 + e3 . Now we cannot afford to take on  e4  as  Bxg4 !, would be too efficient, and White would be able to castle and then pressure our doubled pawns in the center. }
11. Nxe3
12. Bxe3
12. fxe4{ Now it is very easy going forward as ... Bh3 , ... Nd7  would mean trouble for White, considering how hard it would be to castle and how easy our pieces come into action (... Nf6 /... Nc5  or ... Rc8  later on). }
