8. g3( 8.e3 { is a bit too slow, as we can just go for }8...Bf5 { + ... Nbd7  and there ... Nb6  or ... Bb4  to take back the  d5 -pawn. We also have the option to go for }8...e4 { safely (as the  c1 -bishop is not going anywhere) and there go for the usual plan with ... Qe7 , ... Nbd7 , ... Ne5 , ... Rfd8 , ... Rac8  while White can only watch passively. } )
