14. bxa4
15. Nxc4
15. Qc7{ We dream of putting a knight on  c5 . }
16. Be3
16. Na6
17. b4{ White is incredibly smart and uses well the pin on the  a4 -pawn. }
17. Ng4{ We take advantage of the exposed  c4 -knight, and now we want to take on  e3  and later on,  Qb7 - Nc7 , improving our worst piece. I feel the position is severely unbalanced for a London player 😁. }
