7. Bg7
8. Nc4
8. O-O
9. Bd3
9. d6{ As usual, exchanging the light-squared bishop should be great. }
10. Nfd2{ White prevents it. }
10. f5{ We have many nice moves, but I really want you to know that it can be practical to just sacrifice this pawn to free the  g7 -bishop and play with the compensation. }
11. exf5
11. Bb7{ And now ... Nd7 -... Nb6  is coming, and we will have a very nice pressure to the center and the queenside. }
