5. exf6
6. e4{ The only drawback of 4... h6  is that now we cannot play ... f6 -... f5  in one go as  Bb5 +!, would win the pawn. }
6. g6
7. Bd3{ The natural development to prevent us from eventually playing the liberating ... f6 -... f5 . }
7. Bg7
8. Nge2{ White can also try to be conservative about the Knight this way, but we can punish them very quickly. }
8. Nd7
9. O-O
9. a6
10. a4
10. Ne5{ ... c4  is a huge threat. }
11. Ng3
11. h5{ Now White doesn't have an answer to ... h4  + ... f5  threat, opening our bishops and basically killing our opponent in practice. We might even be able to castle first, so our king doesn't get exposed as the  e -file will open. }
