7. Qe7{ This was very trendy back in the day.  h3 - e4 - Bd3  was the mainline by far and with this move we force White to take different paths. }
8. Ra3{ My opponent plays one of the most challenging moves. }
8. g6
9. Nd2
9. Bg7{ 9. ...  Nbd7  to counter 10.  Nc4  with  Ne5 , as we usually do, would've been much healthier and the rook doesn't matter that much. Now we will see some suffering :). }
