12. Ne8
13. e3
13. Nd7
14. a5
14. Ne5{ Everything starts to make sense now. White still has a lot of control on the queenside but it's hard to suggest anything for White to increase the advantage. }( 14...Rb8 15.Na4  )
15. Nb6
