19. Be2
19. Nc7
20. O-O
20. Nxb6
21. Nxb6
21. Bd7{ I finally finish the development. I feel this is a great example to showcase how positions can be bad according to the engine but not really easy how to increase the advantage. Now 22. ...  Bb5  is what we want to do. }
22. f4{ I cannot count how many times my opponent tried to finish me and ended up messing the advantage. }( 22.Re1 Bb5 23.e4  )
22. Qe7
23. Nxd7{ The knight was way too valuable. 23.  Re1  still kept some advantage. }
23. Qxd7
24. f5
24. Re8
25. f6{ White gets obsessed with  Qe1 - Qh4  plans and forgets that I can always go for  Ne8 . }
25. Re5
26. e4
26. Rxe4
27. Qc1( 27.Qd2  )
27. Rxe2
28. Qh6
28. Ne8{ A sad ending for White. Many games in the benoni will be less precise but you will always have similar defensive patterns and White is required to dominate you. It is very unlikely that a direct win appears. }
