1. d4{ This is an example of GM games when both have deep preps. I usually don't condone such deep lines but we are basically reacting every move and looking for counterplay as we are given a question "how can you stop the following threat?". I feel it is a great game to showcase the proactive nature of the Benoni. It's important to notice that this is the exception in the Benoni, deep preps like this are quite rare and White is known for beeing quite well prepared. }
