32. Qc2
33. Bg2{ Creative way to "defend"  f2 . }
33. Kg7{ A subtle prophylaxis to ask White "what are you doing now?". White is threating  d6  and the  Nc4 , so Black cannot move much either. }
34. g4{ White keeps the mutual zugzwang alive. }
34. Qc3{ 34. ...  h6 !! was the subtlest subtlety.  Kg1 / Kh1  fall into  Qb1 +! and  Nb6 , unlocking the hold. If  Kg2   Ne5 !  Qxd6   Nd3 ! and White is losing by force. The bishop cannot move and  h4  runs into  Ne5 ! and the  g4  pawn falls. }
